A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Schools – Water Safety and Swimming – Instructional Content, Plan, and
3 Reporting
4 FOR the purpose of requiring each county board of education to develop certain
5 instructional content on water safety and swimming for public school students in the
6 county; requiring each county board to develop a certain plan regarding access to
7 swimming pools and related facilities for a certain purpose; and generally relating to
8 water safety and swimming and county boards of education.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Education
11 Section 7–452
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Education
17 7–452.
18 (A) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2026, EACH COUNTY BOARD SHALL DEVELOP
19 INSTRUCTIONAL CONTENT ON WATER SAFETY AND SWIMMING THAT IS:
20 (1) INTEGRATED INTO THE HEALTH AND PHYSICAL EDUCATION
21 CURRICULUM FOR EACH PUBLIC SCHOOL IN THE COUNTY; AND
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
