1 (2) AGE–APPROPRIATE FOR STUDENTS IN ELEMENTARY, MIDDLE,
2 AND HIGH SCHOOL.
3 (B) THE INSTRUCTIONAL CONTENT DEVELOPED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF
4 THIS SECTION SHALL INCLUDE OPPORTUNITIES FOR STUDENTS WITH DISABILITIES,
5 IF PRACTICABLE.
6 (C) BEGINNING IN THE 2026–2027 SCHOOL YEAR, EACH COUNTY BOARD
7 SHALL IMPLEMENT THE INSTRUCTIONAL CONTENT DEVELOPED UNDER
8 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION.
9 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
10 (a) (1) On or before December 1, 2025, each county board of education shall
11 develop a plan to ensure public school students in the county have access to swimming pools
12 for swimming and taking swimming and water safety courses.
13 (2) The plan required under this subsection shall:
14 (i) identify strategies to maximize public and private resources to
15 provide access to swimming pools and related facilities for public school students;
16 (ii) identify public and private entities in the local community that
17 could partner with schools to offer access to swimming pools and related facilities to public
18 school students during school operating hours;
19 (iii) identify methods to increase public school student access to
20 swimming pools and related facilities, including costs and transportation, while keeping
21 costs low; and
22 (iv) recommend any necessary changes to policy or law to implement
23 the plan required under paragraph (1) of this subsection and the requirements of § 7–452
24 of the Education Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act.
25 (b) On or before December 15, 2025, each county board shall submit a copy of the
26 plan developed under subsection (a) of this section to the State Department of Education.
27 (c) On or before January 1, 2026, the State Department of Education shall
28 compile the reports submitted under subsection (b) of this section and submit a report that
29 includes all the county boards’ plans to the General Assembly, in accordance with §
30 2–1257 of the State Government Article.
31 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
32 1, 2025. Section 2 of this Act shall remain effective for a period of 1 year and, at the end of
33 June 30, 2026, Section 2 of this Act, with no further action required by the General
34 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.

